  <title>amount fraction <em>x</em> (<em>y</em> for gaseous mixtures)</title>
  <synonyms>
    <item>mole fraction</item>
  </synonyms>
  <index>quantity</index>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Amount of a constituent divided by the total amount of all constituents in the mixture. It is also called mole fraction. Amount fraction is equal to the number fraction: the number of entities of one constituent divided by the total number of entities in the mixture.</text>
